casebody.data:
In re Blakeslee. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. November 3, 1890.)

Argued before Daly, C. J., and Bischoff and Pryor, JJ.

G. M. Baker, for appellant. Geo. M. Pinney, Jr,, for respondent. Per Curiam.

The order will be reversed upon the ground that the pro.ceedings for an accounting should have been instituted by a citation instead of by an order to show cause. Assignment Act, §§ 11-20, inclusive.
